Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#setOf\">}</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#setOf\">}</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringLike\">SpringLike</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringLike.mk","kind":"ctor","line":37,"name":"SpringLike.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/FMLJohn/Hochster/blob/9bf7d2854bbcf7e2b66bf5d29463e455d494e9af/Hochster/Section3.lean#L37-L37"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringLike\"><span class=\"name\">SpringLike</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> (max (max u_1 u_2) (u_3 + 1))</div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a topological space `X` and a commutative ring `A`, `SpringLike X A` holds if `X` is a\nspectral space and there exist `i : X → Type*` and `h : A →+* Π x : X, i x` such that:\n1. for any `x : X`, `i x` is an integral domain;\n2. `h` is injective;\n3. for any `a : A`, `{ x : X | h a x ≠ 0 }` is open and compact;\n4. `{ { x : X | h a x ≠ 0 } | a : A }` is an open basis for `X`.\nLater we will see that `SpringLike 𝔸.X 𝔸.A` holds for any `𝔸 : SpringCat`, and that for any\ntopolgical space `X` and commutative ring `A` with `SpringLike X A` there exists some\n`𝔸 : SpringCat` such that `𝔸.X` and `𝔸.A` are defined as `X` and `A` respectively.\n","docLink":"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringLike","kind":"structure","line":26,"name":"SpringLike","sourceLink":"https://github.com/FMLJohn/Hochster/blob/9bf7d2854bbcf7e2b66bf5d29463e455d494e9af/Hochster/Section3.lean#L26-L47"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringCat.range_isClosed\"><span class=\"name\">SpringCat</span>.<span class=\"name\">range_isClosed</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringCat\">SpringCat</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#IsClosed\">IsClosed</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Operations.html#Set.range\">Set.range</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">self</span>.<a href=\"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringCat.f\">f</a></span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringCat.range_isClosed","kind":"theorem","line":24,"name":"SpringCat.range_isClosed","sourceLink":"https://github.com/FMLJohn/Hochster/blob/9bf7d2854bbcf7e2b66bf5d29463e455d494e9af/Hochster/Section3.lean#L24-L24"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringCat.range_de