/span>.<a href=\"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringCat.A\">A</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">y</span>.<a href=\"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringCat.A\">A</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">commRing</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span>.<a href=\"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringCat.commRing\">commRing</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HEq\">≍</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">y</span>.<a href=\"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringCat.commRing\">commRing</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span>.<a href=\"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringCat.f\">f</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HEq\">≍</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">y</span>.<a href=\"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringCat.f\">f</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">y</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringCat.ext","kind":"theorem","line":14,"name":"SpringCat.ext","sourceLink":"https://github.com/FMLJohn/Hochster/blob/9bf7d2854bbcf7e2b66bf5d29463e455d494e9af/Hochster/Section3.lean#L14-L14"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringCat\"><span class=\"name\">SpringCat</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> (max (u_1 + 1) (u_2 + 1))</div></div>","info":{"doc":"The category of springs. Mathematically, a spring is a pair `(X, A)` where `A` is a commutative\nring whose nilradical is `{0}`, and `X` is a dense patch in `PrimeSpectrum A`. In this structure,\nwe express this idea by declaring that there is an embedding `f : X → PrimeSpectrum A` and that\n`Set.range f` is a dense patch in `PrimeSpectrum A`.\n","docLink":"./Hochster/Section3.html#SpringCat","kind":"structure","line":8,"name":"SpringCat","sourceLink":"https://github.com/FMLJohn/Hochster/blob/9bf7d2854bbcf7e2b66bf5d29463e455d494e9af/Hochster/Section3.lean#L8-L24"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Category.Basic","Mathlib.RingTheory.Spectrum.Prime.Topology","Hochster.Section2"],"instances":[{"className":"CategoryTheory.Category","name":"SpringCat.instCategory","typeNames":["SpringCat"]},{"className":"SpectralSpace","name":"SpringCat.instSpectralSpaceX","typeNames":["SpringCat.X"]},{"className":"IsReduced","name":"Pi.isReduced_of_forall_isReduced","typeNames":[]}],"name":"Hochster.Section3"}